title: Paths Search Priority
body:
## Situation
Every time __TooBasic__ loads configuration files it follow this steps:
* Site config file inside `site/configs/`.
    * `config.php` first
    * and then `config_shell.php` or `config_http.php`
* All modules configurations (sorted by name in reverse order).
    * `config.php` first
    * and then `config_shell.php` or `config_http.php`
* __TooBasic__ system configurations inside the system-directory.
    * `config.php` first
    * and then `config_shell.php` or `config_http.php`
* Site main config file inside `site/`

## Problem
This kind of default behavior has problems when a modules depends on configuration given by another module.

## What to do.
Implement a mechanism that uses dependencies specified inside module manifests to guess the proper way of loading module configurations.
Also, this mechanism should have a way to cache such analysis to avoid performance issues related to manifest readings.

title: Options in Params
body:
## What to do
Add a new property in called `opt` for singleton `Params`. Such property should provide special access to singleton `Shell\Options` with this features:
* It should only be present when it is a shell execution.
* It should provide access to options using their names as keys.
* It should implement an interpreter similar to `ParamsStack`.
* `__get()` should return:
    * the given value of a requested parameter.
    * `true` or `false` depending on its activation status, only when it's a parameter without value.
    * `null` if it's not given.
* `__isset()` should return `true` when an option is defined and activated.
* `all()` should return a list of activated options.
* Hide methods:
    * `__set()`
    * `addValue()`
    * `addValues()`
* Return dummy values on methods:
    * `debugs()`
    * `hasDebugs()`

Also document this behavior.

title: Sub-representation expansion
body:
## Reason
Since it's common that a table has columns with values that are IDs of some other tables, and if all this tables has their own representations and factories, it would be interesting and easier if the user can to such sub-representation without writing any custom code.

## What to do
Create a mechanism for _representations_ that allow the expansion and use of _sub-representation_ represented by a column value (considered to be a foreign ID).

Document this new behavior.

## Features
* A column points to a _sub-representation_ should be specified in a new _core property_ (a list).
* Each _sub-representation_ column specification should:
    * Use the column name without prefixes as key.
    * Specify which factory can provide access to a sub-item.
    * Specify the method name to access it to avoid method names collisions.
        * When not given, the column name should be used as method name.
* Magic method `__call()` should expect this new methods.
* Method `toArray()` should also use _sub-representations_ when they were expanded.
* Representations constructors should clean up the new _core property_ to ensure required specifications.

title: Multi-table Selects in Query Adapters
body:
## What to do
_Query Adapters_ should allow a way to join tables in selects. This will provide a generic way to build this:
```sql
select  * 
from    tst_master, 
        tst_children 
where   chl_parent = mas_id
 and    chl_name like :chl_name 
order by mas_id ASC
```
